snippet: Some signs, like bidding wars and more people at open houses, indicate that the New York City real estate market has turned the corner.
abstract: Huge increases in open house traffic and a quickening pace of sales may be signs that New York City's real estate market is picking up, but industry is cautiously watching to see if buyer confidence will last or if upward trend is fleeting.
lead_paragraph: Some signs, like bidding wars and more people at open houses, indicate that the New York City real estate market has turned the corner.
